{
  "designRationale": {
    "layoutDecisions": "The layout employs a vertical list for settings, optimizing for mobile screen real estate and intuitive top-to-bottom user flow.  Spacing between items is consistent at 24dp for visual breathing room and tap target clarity. Padding is added at the top and bottom for a less cramped feel.  The width is fixed at 375dp, suitable for standard mobile screen dimensions.",
    "userFlowReasoning": "The user journey prioritizes ease of access to core settings.  Critical settings are listed prominently at the top, while secondary settings are placed below.  Each setting is represented by a tappable list item, providing clear visual feedback. Destructive actions (account deletion) involve confirmation dialogs to prevent accidental actions.  The top app bar includes a back button, supporting easy navigation.",
    "componentChoices": "The `appbar` component is used for the top bar, providing a standard navigation pattern with title and back button.  `list-item` components are utilized for individual settings. Each `list-item` displays the setting label and an arrow icon for navigation. The `Bottom navigation` component is used for app-wide navigation.",
    "visualHierarchy": "Visual hierarchy is achieved through vertical arrangement (top-to-bottom importance), clear labels, and consistent styling using the design system's color styles for text and background elements. The size and weight of text is also used to create visual hierarchy."
  }
}
---RATIONALE-SEPARATOR---
